label("F",(8,7.5),E); label("E",(8,2.5),NW); label("A",(4,0),SW);
dot((11.5,-1)); dot((9,-5)); dot((5,-4.5));
label("D",(11.5,-1),E); label("C",(9,-5),SE); label("B",(5,-4.5),SW);
label("$108^\circ$",(1.5,4.5),NW);
label("$120^\circ$",(6.5,4.5),NE);
[/asy]

Angles $AED$ and $AEF$ are supplementary, so $\angle AED=180^\circ-120^\circ=60^\circ$.  Therefore, $\angle DEF=108^\circ+60^\circ=\boxed{168^\circ}$.

